list-item.p:
J-T coolers of 1 W at 80 K refrigeration capacity, 7.20 mm diameter, 27 mm coiled length:


fixed orifice type;

self-regulating type.

sec.p:
The liquefaction was observed continuously even when the bottle pressure fell just below the set pressure output (14 MPa) level of regulator. The experiment was continued even after the bottle pressure fell below the preset regulator output pressure to record the lowest bottle pressure needed for continued cooling. Bottle pressure and cooling temperatures were recorded at regular intervals. The observations made were:


cooling temperature: 80 K ± 0.5 K;

make time: 1 min;

bottle duration time: 57 min;

lowest bottle pressure for continued cooling: 7 MPa;

mean flow rate (normal liter/minute): 9.3;

temperature stability: ±0.5 K.

The J-T cooler of the basic fixed orifice J-T cooler system as mentioned in the section entitled ‘Basic cooling system’ was replaced by self-regulating cooler of same size and refrigeration capacity. The experiment was carried out and following observations were made.


cooling temperature: 80 K ± 1 K;

make time: 1 minute 45 s at no load;

bottle duration time: 210 min;

mean flow rate (normal liter/minute):


during make phase: 5.5;

after make phase (bellow active phase): 1.5.


temperature stability: ±1.0 K.

The following observations were recorded:


